# Compiler Reports Module
#
# Specialized report types for the Simple language compiler.
# Provides:
# - EasyFixReport: Machine-applicable fixes with confidence levels
# - CompilerDiagnostic: Base class for compiler diagnostics
# - ParseError, TypeError, NameError: Specialized diagnostic factories
# - LintWarning: Lint rule violations
# - Adapters for backward compatibility with legacy types
#
# # Quick Start
#
# ```simple
# import std.report.compiler
#
# # Create a type error
# val diag = TypeError.mismatch("i64", "text", location)
#     .with_note("types must match for assignment")
#     .with_help("convert the value with .to_string()")
#
# # Create a lint warning with auto-fix
# val fix = EasyFixReport.safe("L:deprecated_if_let", "Replace 'if let' with 'if val'")
#     .with_replacement(Replacement.at(file, start, end, line, col, "if val"))
#
# val warning = LintWarning.deprecated("if let", Some("if val"), location)
#     .with_easy_fix(fix)
# ```
#
# # Error Codes
#
# | Code | Category | Description |
# |------|----------|-------------|
# | E0001 | Parse | Unexpected token |
# | E0002 | Parse | Unexpected EOF |
# | E0003 | Parse | Invalid syntax |
# | E0308 | Type | Type mismatch |
# | E0282 | Type | Cannot infer type |
# | E0425 | Name | Undefined variable |
# | E0412 | Name | Undefined type |
# | E0428 | Name | Duplicate definition |
# | W0001 | Lint | Unused variable |
# | W0002 | Lint | Unused import |
# | W0003 | Lint | Deprecated feature |
#
# # Fix Confidence Levels
#
# | Level | Description | Auto-apply? |
# |-------|-------------|-------------|
# | MachineApplicable | Safe, verified correct | Yes |
# | MaybeIncorrect | Probably correct | Review first |
# | HasPlaceholders | Contains <#...#> markers | No |
# | Unspecified | Unknown confidence | No |

